Content":[{"text":"This is similar to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional\/dependency(_:_:)","isActive":true},{"text":", except it allows you to mutate a dependency value","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directly. This can be handy when you want to alter a dependency but still use its current","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, suppose you want to see when a particular endpoint of a dependency gets called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in your application. You can override that endpoint to insert a breakpoint or print statement,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but still call out to the original endpoint:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["  Feature()","    .transformDependency(\\.speechClient) { speechClient in","      speechClient.requestAuthorization = {","        print(\"requestAuthorization\")","        try await speechClient.requestAuthorization()","      }","    }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also transform "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency values at once by using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\.self"},{"text":" key path:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Feature()","  .transformDependency(\\.self) { dependencyValues in","    \/\/ Access to all dependencies in here","  }"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The trailing closure of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional\/transformDependency(_:transform:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is called for every"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action sent to the reducer, and so you can expect it to be called many times in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application’s lifecycle. This means you should typically not create dependencies in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closure as that will cause a new dependency to be created everytime an action is sent.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Warning","type":"aside","style":"warning"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional\/Reducer-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/Effect":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/effect","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Effect","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Effect","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Effect"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/Swift/Optional/transformDependency(_:transform:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/swift\/optional\/transformdependency(_:transform:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Transform a reducer’s dependency value at the specified key path with the given function."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional\/transformDependency(_:transform:)","kind":"symbol","title":"transformDependency(_:transform:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"transformD